Reasoning: The paper deals with classification performance of K-NN and CNNs, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the role of label noise, which is a common problem in machine learning, suggesting that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper derives an analytic expression for the K-NN classification error, which may be of interest to researchers in the field of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
